      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structADC__InitTypeDef_1aa72b0cc3e8dac3a30097cf12093c42a7" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t ADC_InitTypeDef::NbrOfConversion</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>NbrOfConversion</name>
        <qualifiedname>ADC_InitTypeDef::NbrOfConversion</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Specify the number of ranks that will be converted within the regular group sequencer. This parameter is dependent on ScanConvMode:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>sequencer configured to fully configurable: Number of ranks in the scan sequence is configurable using this parameter. Note: After the first call of &apos;<ref refid="group__ADC__Exported__Functions__Group1_1ga33ddb73d4880bd425aaa43c5c52bb13a" kindref="member">HAL_ADC_Init()</ref>&apos;, each rank corresponding to parameter &quot;NbrOfConversion&quot; must be set using &apos;<ref refid="group__ADC__Exported__Functions__Group3_1ga96f4317420984bec9226f7d93cb36f1b" kindref="member">HAL_ADC_ConfigChannel()</ref>&apos;. Afterwards, when all needed sequencer ranks are set, parameter &apos;NbrOfConversion&apos; can be updated without modifying configuration of sequencer ranks (sequencer ranks above &apos;NbrOfConversion&apos; are discarded).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>sequencer configured to not fully configurable: Number of ranks in the scan sequence is defined by number of channels set in the sequence. This parameter is discarded. This parameter must be a number between Min_Data = 1 and Max_Data = 8. Note: This parameter must be modified when no conversion is on going on regular group (ADC disabled, or ADC enabled without continuous mode or external trigger that could launch a conversion). </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" line="158" column="12" bodyfile="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" bodystart="158" bodyend="-1"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structADC__InitTypeDef_1afb62fa7128d7c97d53d2eb170ad467eb" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type><ref refid="group__Exported__types_1gac9a7e9a35d2513ec15c3b537aaa4fba1" kindref="member">FunctionalState</ref></type>
        <definition>FunctionalState ADC_InitTypeDef::DiscontinuousConvMode</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>DiscontinuousConvMode</name>
        <qualifiedname>ADC_InitTypeDef::DiscontinuousConvMode</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Specify whether the conversions sequence of ADC group regular is performed in Complete-sequence/Discontinuous-sequence (main sequence subdivided in successive parts). Discontinuous mode is used only if sequencer is enabled (parameter &apos;ScanConvMode&apos;). If sequencer is disabled, this parameter is discarded. Discontinuous mode can be enabled only if continuous mode is disabled. If continuous mode is enabled, this parameter setting is discarded. This parameter can be set to ENABLE or DISABLE. Note: On this STM32 series, ADC group regular number of discontinuous ranks increment is fixed to one-by-one. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" line="176" column="19" bodyfile="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" bodystart="176" bodyend="-1"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structADC__InitTypeDef_1a5c0078be814bfe2608ae5758826eafb8" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t ADC_InitTypeDef::NbrOfDiscConversion</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>NbrOfDiscConversion</name>
        <qualifiedname>ADC_InitTypeDef::NbrOfDiscConversion</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Specifies the number of discontinuous conversions in which the main sequence of ADC group regular (parameter NbrOfConversion) will be subdivided. If parameter &apos;DiscontinuousConvMode&apos; is disabled, this parameter is discarded. This parameter must be a number between Min_Data = 1 and Max_Data = 8. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" line="187" column="12" bodyfile="/home/runner/work/cubesat/cubesat/eps/v1/firmware/bootstrap/Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32l4xx_hal_adc.h" bodystart="187" bodyend="-1"/>
